Yes, **the final model is SemDINO-style**, but **we are not at the SemDINO training stage yet**.

Think of your project as:

```text
Stage 1
↓
Prepare semantic datasets

Stage 2
↓
Train semantic understanding

Stage 3
↓
Create bi-temporal pairs

Stage 4
↓
Train SemDINO
```

Right now you are in **Stage 1**.

***

## Why we generated vegetation masks

SemDINO does **not** train directly from GeoJSON polygons.

It ultimately needs semantic supervision such as:

```text
T1 semantic map
T2 semantic map
change map
```

For vegetation we currently have:

```text
RGB image
+
Vegetation polygons
```

So the first step is:

```text
GeoJSON polygons
↓
Raster masks
↓
Training labels
```

which you have now successfully created.

***

## What happens next

For vegetation:

```text
RGB
↓
Vegetation Mask
```

We create image-mask tiles:

```text
512 x 512

images/
masks/
```

Example:

```text
tile_001.png
tile_001_mask.png
```

***

## Then DINO, not SegFormer

Since your final goal is SemDINO-style:

I would not spend much effort on SegFormer.

Instead:

```text
DINOv3 features
+
light segmentation decoder
```

for vegetation.

Purpose:

```text
Learn vegetation semantics
```

not change detection yet.

***

## Final Architecture Actually Looks Like

### Vegetation Training

Current stage:

```text
Vegetation Image
+
Vegetation Polygon
↓
Vegetation Mask
↓
Tiles
↓
DINOv3 Encoder
↓
Vegetation Decoder
↓
Vegetation Prediction
```

***

### Road Training

```text
Road Image
+
Road Polygon
↓
Road Mask
↓
DINOv3 Encoder
↓
Road Decoder
```

***

### Building Training

```text
Building Image
+
Building Polygons
↓
Building Masks
↓
DINOv3 Encoder
↓
Building Decoder
```

***

### Water Training

```text
Water Image
+
Water Polygon
↓
Water Mask
↓
DINOv3 Encoder
↓
Water Decoder
```

***

## Then SemDINO

After all four semantic datasets exist:

```text
Vegetation
Road
Building
Water
```

you create:

```text
T1 Image
T2 Image
```

pairs.

Then SemDINO receives:

```text
Image T1
Image T2
```

and learns:

```text
Semantic T1
Semantic T2
Binary Change
Class Change
```

***

## Your Immediate Next Step

Not SemDINO yet.

Do this:

```text
Vegetation GeoJSON
↓
Vegetation Mask
✓ Done

Vegetation Mask
↓
512x512 Tiles
↓
Train DINOv3 Semantic Vegetation Model
```

Then repeat for:

```text
Road
Building
Water
```

Only after all semantic datasets are ready do we build the dual-branch **SemDINO change detector**.

So **yes, the final model is SemDINO-style**, but the vegetation-mask generation you just completed is the correct first step needed before SemDINO can be trained.
